<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,153,575]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">
b) Since the taxonomic interpretation of Hübner’s pictures is far from being unequivocal, because differences between adults of the 1 
<superScript attach="left" box="[406,417,188,202]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">st</superScript>
and 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[484,500,188,202]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">nd</superScript>
generation of both the eastern and the western ‘dappled whites’ are strong, and since truly diagnostic species-specific differences are found only in the preimaginal stages (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Back, W." box="[1162,1284,225,251]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" pagination="225 - 243" refId="ref4912" refString="Back, W. (1979) Zur Biologie der europaischen und nord west afrikanischen Populationen von Euchloe ausonia Hubner 1804 (Lep. Pieridae). Atalanta, 10 (3), 225 - 243, figs 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="1979">Back 1979</bibRefCitation>
) and in DNA COI sequences (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Back, W. &amp; Miller, M. A. &amp; Opler, O. A." box="[378,564,261,287]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" pagination="1 - 14" refId="ref5008" refString="Back, W., Miller, M. A. &amp; Opler, O. A. (2011) Genetic, phenetic, and distributional relationships of Nearctic Euchloe (Pieridae, Pierinae, Anthocharidini). Journal of the Lepidopterists' Society, 65 (1), 1 - 14. https: // doi. org / 10.18473 / lepi. v 65 i 1. a 1" type="journal article" year="2011">
Back 
<emphasis box="[442,498,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
), this name was taken to represent each of the already mentioned taxa, at various taxonomic ranks, depending on authors. More precisely, the name [
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[937,1019,297,323]" class="Insecta" family="Papilionidae" genus="Papilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[937,1019,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">Papilio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
] 
<taxonomicName authority="Hubner, [1804]" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1804" box="[1035,1299,296,323]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Euchloe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ausonia">
<emphasis box="[1035,1124,298,323]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">ausonia</emphasis>
Hübner, [1804]
</taxonomicName>
was applied either i) to the ‘western dappled white’ (
<bibRefCitation author="Ochsenheimer, F." box="[596,825,333,359]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" refId="ref7232" refString="Ochsenheimer, F. (1808) Die Schmetterlinge von Europa. 1 (2). G. Fleischer der Junger, Leipzig, xxx + 240 + [1] pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 50612" type="book" year="1808">Ochsenheimer 1808</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Staudinger, O." box="[836,1021,333,359]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" pagination="1 - 411" refId="ref7496" refString="Staudinger, O. (1901) Erster Theil: Famil. Papilionidae-Hepialidae. In: Staudinger, O. &amp; Rebel, H., Catalog der Lepidopteren des Palaearktischen Faunengebietes. Dritte Auflage. R. Friedlander &amp; Sohn, Berlin, pp. i-xxxii + 1 - 411. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 120482" type="book chapter" year="1901">Staudinger 1901</bibRefCitation>
, etc.), or ii) to the ‘mountain dappled white’ (
<bibRefCitation author="Kirby, W. F." box="[238,372,369,395]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" refId="ref7024" refString="Kirby, W. F. (1871) A synonymic catalogue of diurnal Lepidoptera. John van Voorst, London, viii + 883 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 11905" type="book" year="1871">Kirby 1871</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rothschild, W." box="[386,576,369,395]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" pagination="301 - 305" refId="ref7431" refString="Rothschild, W. (1914) A preliminary account of the Lepidopteran Fauna of Guelt-es-Stel, Central Algeria, Novitates Zoologicae, 21, 301 - 305. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 16331" type="journal article" year="1914">Rothschild 1914</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Oberthur, C." box="[589,759,369,395]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" pagination="51 - 61" refId="ref7207" refString="Oberthur, C. (1914) Anthocharis crameri Butler. Etudes de Lepidopterologie comparee, 10, 51 - 61. [texted]" type="journal article" year="1914">Oberthür 1914</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hemming, F. A." box="[772,952,369,395]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" pagination="493 - 504" refId="ref6087" refString="Hemming, F. A. (1931) New material regarding the dates of the plates of the Papiliones in Jacob Hubner's &quot; Sammlung europaischer Schmetterlinge &quot;, with notes on the synonymy and type localities of certain species described therein. Transactions of the entomological Society of London, 79 (3), 493 - 504. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1931. tb 00713. x" type="journal article" year="1931">Hemming 1931</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bernardi, G." box="[966,1132,368,395]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" pagination="66 - 103" refId="ref5169" refString="Bernardi, G. (1945) Etudes sur le genre Euchloe Hb. (Lep. Pieridae). Miscellanea entomologica; Revue entomologique internationale, 42 (6), 66 - 103, pls. IV-VI." type="journal article" year="1945">Bernardi 1945</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bernardi, G." box="[1146,1205,369,395]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref5209" refString="Bernardi, G. (1947) La nomenclature de quelques formes europeennes de l' Euchloe ausonia Hb. (= belia Auct.). Miscellanea entomologica; Revue entomologique internationale, 44 (1), 1 - 24." type="journal article" year="1947">1947</bibRefCitation>
, Forster &amp; Wohlfart 1955, 
