<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,153,575]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">
Summarising, it is exclusively on the subjective interpretation of Hübner’s figures and on the derivation of its name from the land where the ancient people of the Ausoni used to live, i.e. in central and southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1273,1325,477,503]" name="Italy" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">Italy</collectingCountry>
, that [
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" class="Insecta" family="Papilionidae" genus="Papilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">Papilio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
] 
<taxonomicName authority="Hubner, [1804]" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1804" box="[218,483,512,539]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Euchloe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ausonia">
<emphasis box="[218,307,514,539]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">ausonia</emphasis>
Hübner, [1804]
</taxonomicName>
is now considered the correct name to identify the butterfly colloquially known as the ‘eastern dappled white’.
